    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh sorry, i forgot to attach it. here it is:\n\n[SECTION 4.2: PRICE ADJUSTMENTS]\nThe Supplier reserves the right to implement a price adjustment of up to 5% per month during defined peak seasonal periods (as outlined in Appendix B) without prior written notice to the Client, provided such adjustments are reflected in the subsequent billing cycle. All other pricing changes shall be subject to mutual written agreement between both parties.\n\nany risks there? looks pretty standard to me but i want your professional take. does this allow them to change rates unexpectedly?",
